This amazing collaborative animation between @c_bass3d and @neoporkog beautifully captures with amazing sights we will see when Starship leaves Earth for the first time!

You can watch the full YouTube video here:
https://youtu.be/iFt_LsFRFEQ
⚠️it's 8 minutes of pure awesomeness⚠️
.
.
Follow @neoporkog and @c_bass3d on here aswell as twitter for more amazing work!
.
.

.

node.text:
Orbital Combat! 🤜🤛

Duke it out in Orbital Combat and become the greatest spacecraft of all time!

Tired of arguing on the internet over which rocket is best? Orbital Combat is the game created to settle those disputes! With a large selection of characters and arenas, you'll be able to create any scenario you'd like when it comes to fighting spacecrafts!

20 characters to play as or fight against
Choose from 20 different characters inspired by real spacecraft such as SpaceX's Starship and NASA's Perseverance Rover. Each character is equipped with unique animations, move-sets, and special abilities.

10 arenas to fight on
Fight on arenas ranging from locations such as launch complexes, droneship fleets, and even martian dunes.

Fight in Instant Action or Destroy All Rockets mode
Easily select 2 fighters and an arena for a quick matchup in instant action. Embark on a journey to become the greatest rocket in Destroy All Rockets mode where you will have to fight through most of the different characters and come out on top.

.
Credits to Orbital Combat

https://store.steampowered.com/app/1693780/Orbital_Combat/

node.text:
Many companies are reliant on the forecasted prices of the next generation launchers. Starship is extremely appetising to small organisations such as @conexresearch as it allows them to design vehicles with more freedom and deploy them for a fraction of the cost.

Conex Research:
Let's compare three heavy-lift orbital launch vehicles: 🚀🚀

SLS (NASA), New Glenn (Blue Origin) and Starship (SpaceX), all of which are great for delivering large quantities of useful payloads and scientific missions into space, but if we will take into account the ratio of the price / mass of the payload per kg Starship becomes more attractive transport tool for Arcanum science mission. In our mission, as a launcher case study we selected Starship due to these costs proposed by SpaceX. These prices are subject to change as all three vehicles are undergoing development.

Credit to @nasa , @blueorigin and @everydayastronaut for the great visuals!

@ConexResearch is an International research group, working online on the #ArcanumMission to explore Neptune, Triton and KBOs. Looking for students/early careers in STEM!
.
